website_summaries.verdict: Ideal for beginners and intermediate players. Versatile and high-quality build and warm tone.
pros: Dreadnought cutaway body allows easier access to lower frets
Quality mahogany finish and black and white binding
Durable chrome tuning knobs and attractive "mother of pearl" style acrylic surrounding  the sound hole
Package comes with case, tuner, strings, instructional DVD, and guitar picks
cons: Neck width is narrower than full sized guitars

customer_reviews.title: Dissapointed
customer_reviews.text: Buyer's remorse to the fullest. The low open E string buzzes terribly and the B and High E sound flat and like strings that are very old. They contacted me by email thanking you for buying their product and I responded but have since heard nothing 5 days now. I purchased an Ibanez for half the price that has an amazing sound that I gave an awesome review on and I would have liked to do the same on this product.
customer_reviews.author: Ethan  W. Ferry

customer_reviews.title: Excellent set!
customer_reviews.text: Beautiful guitar. The case is amazing. All the bonuses that come with it are nice. The way I broke it down.. the guitar itself is worth the price. Then everything else is basically free. The case is easily worth over $100! The only thing you need is the amp and some better picks.
customer_reviews.author: Momo6

customer_reviews.title: Definite Buy!
customer_reviews.text: I've been playing for over 45 years, and I'll have to say that my expectations for this price level guitar were pretty low. That said, this Fender guitar far exceeded my expectations and I'm thrilled with my guitar. The sound quality is awesome. The tones are crisp, clear, full, and rich. Is this a concert level guitar, of course not. But for this price, the guitar is a steal.
customer_reviews.author: Juan Martinez

customer_reviews.title: Mine was lousy

I guess I got a Monday morning lemon I'm stuck with my epiphone great guitar ,,,but this fender , ? nahhh ,it just sucks

customer_reviews.title: Warped fretboard.
customer_reviews.text: I loved this guitar for the first 3 months. Sounds great at the price point. But at the turn of the first cold weather, the fretboard warped and now the 14th fret is too high and I get buzzing on every note below the 14th fret regardless of setup (within reason). This is my first acoustic guitar purchase (been playing an old Yamaha hand-me-down previously), and I am very disappointed in Fender.

customer_reviews.title: Really heckin rad package deal.

The case feels like it will hold up for a good while. I love the built in tuner as well but even if that craps out, they included a stand alone tuner which also works flawlessly. 10/10
